claim.claim-text:
1. A method for hand-off of a communication session in a mobile wireless communication system, in which the communication session of a mobile unit on a first call path is transferred from a serving base station to a target base station, the method comprising: 
(a) establishing a second call path from the serving base station to the target base station via a switch; 
(b) combining the second call path with the communication session on the first call path to form a multiway communication session; 
(c) providing for the mobile unit to communicate with the target base station for continuation of the communication session through a first leg of the multiway communication session; and 
(d) releasing the serving base station from a second leg of the multiway communication session.

2. The method of claim 1, wherein step (a) further comprises: 
transmitting a call set up message to the switch; 
transmitting a first information message to the switch specifying a directory number of a terminal of the target base station.
